Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.67,0:00:32.78,black-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(542.286,239.143)}pebbles
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.54,0:00:38.58,black-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(334.857,183.714)}Maybe if I...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.00,0:01:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢a crow can think｣
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.00,0:01:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢can think... can think｣
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.00,0:01:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Observe, then propose a hypothesis, experiment and consider results.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.00,0:01:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Lean the way of scientific thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.00,0:01:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin with a thinking observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.00,0:01:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When we look at the water in a bathtub...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.00,0:01:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We can see it has some color.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.00,0:01:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's greenish blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.00,0:01:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But water ought to be transparent. Why can we see a color?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.00,0:01:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it's only because we're looking at it in the bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.00,0:02:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try looking at it out of the bathtub, in a glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.00,0:02:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no color. It's clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.00,0:02:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,To make sure, let's compare to an empty glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.00,0:02:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The one with water has a little more color but
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.00,0:02:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it's hard to tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.00,0:02:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What will happen if we increase the number of glasses?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.00,0:02:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The light color has increased, and we can see some blue, can't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.00,0:02:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We can see blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.00,0:02:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But the water's color isn't significant.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.00,0:02:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But perhaps it's the color of the glass itself which makes the color visible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.00,0:03:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We prepare a long tube.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.00,0:03:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Both ends are closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.00,0:03:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We fill it with water via a hole on top.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.00,0:03:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's full.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.00,0:03:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When we look at it from the side it appears transparent.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.00,0:03:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But when we look lengthwise...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.00,0:03:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it's blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.00,0:03:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's quite similar to the color in the bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.00,0:03:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So is the water blue because of its depth?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.00,0:03:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try comparig it to the bath water.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.00,0:04:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Its appears to be the same color but the blue in the bath water is a little deeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.00,0:04:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it because there's more water there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.00,0:04:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try pulling the plug.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.00,0:04:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What will happen to the color?
