Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.00,0:06:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Today's experiment
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.00,0:06:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,uses a clear super-ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.00,0:06:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We put the ball into a round container of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.00,0:06:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If we do this what will happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.00,0:06:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks much bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.00,0:06:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The container is acting like a lens.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.00,0:06:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.00,0:06:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we put a small sticker on the ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.00,0:07:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When we look at this from the opposite side...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.00,0:07:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks big.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.00,0:07:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this is the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.00,0:07:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If put the ball in the water like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.00,0:07:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,our view of the sticker...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.00,0:07:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How will it change?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.46,0:07:36.63,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(127,80)}1. It will look even bigger
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.63,0:07:36.63,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(109,127)}2. It won't change.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.63,0:07:36.63,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(117,177)}3. It will look smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.00,0:07:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then let's try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.00,0:07:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll present the answer at the end of the program.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.00,0:07:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, think about it very hard, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.09,0:08:02.13,white-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(329.778,103.778)}Today's Discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.09,0:08:02.13,white-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(395.667,278.556)}Holes in the Ground
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.13,0:08:05.76,white-large,,0,0,0,,Not worth mentioning
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.76,0:08:08.67,white-large,,0,0,0,,but still I want to tell it to someone
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.63,0:08:12.40,white-large,,0,0,0,,today's discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.44,0:08:15.84,white-large,,0,0,0,,casually looking beneath a roadside tree
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.84,0:08:18.81,white-large,,0,0,0,,there's a many holes of some kind
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.81,0:08:20.95,white-large,,0,0,0,,what are these holes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.61,0:08:25.95,white-large,,0,0,0,,Looking at the tree trunk
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.95,0:08:29.35,white-large,,0,0,0,,Cicada
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.53,0:08:43.30,white-large,,0,0,0,,How wonderful. Today's discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.30,0:08:48.57,white-large,,0,0,0,,And tomorrow there will probably be another.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.47,0:08:53.18,black-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(358.222,41.556)}one each day
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.47,0:08:53.18,black-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(422.222,158.889)}today's discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.98,0:09:01.92,black-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(314,103)}Q: If we we put the ball in the water, how will the size of the sticker change?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.98,0:09:01.92,black-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(368,200)}1. It will look even bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.98,0:09:01.92,black-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(346,248)}2. It won't change.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.98,0:09:01.92,black-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(358,298)}3. It will look smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.00,0:08:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the answer from earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.00,0:09:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone did you think about it carefully?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.00,0:09:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's try it for real.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.00,0:09:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What will happen, please look carefully, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.00,0:09:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you get it? The answer is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.77,0:09:24.14,white-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(325,307)}3. It looks smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.00,0:09:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though the ball itself looks bigger...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.00,0:09:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the sticker looks smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.00,0:09:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you think that is?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.00,0:09:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well at first the sticker looked big because the light was bent.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.00,0:09:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Light has a property so that when it travels between different materials...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.00,0:09:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when it traverses that boundary the light is bent.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.00,0:09:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And the ball in the water...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.00,0:09:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,From here on we think for ourselves.
